# Swiper Standards

This project uses **Swiper 12.x** via a global `window.Swiper` (registered from `src/js/swiper-init.js`). Modules (Navigation, Pagination, Autoplay, FreeMode, Scrollbar, A11y, EffectFade, Thumbs) are registered globally via `Swiper.use([...])` — no per-block module imports needed. Call `new Swiper(...)` directly.

Block SCSS rules are always nested inside an outer `.{slug}-section` wrapper; child classes are plain (`.slide`, `.controls`, `.card`) — no BEM `__` prefixes. Uniqueness comes from nesting, not prefixes.

---

## 1. HTML Structure (PHP partial)

> **MANDATORY:** Always render the pagination and navigation via the project's shared template parts — `template-parts/swiper-pagination.php` and `template-parts/swiper-navigation.php`. **Do NOT** hand-write the pagination `<div>`, the `.swiper-navigation` wrapper, the prev/next buttons, or their SVG icons in your block PHP. The template parts already produce the correct markup, classes, ARIA, and SVG icons; their styling lives in the global partials `_swiper-pagination.scss` and `_swiper-navigation.scss`.
>
> Likewise, **do NOT** write block-specific SCSS for layout, sizing, or shape of `.swiper-pagination`, `.swiper-pagination-line`, `.swiper-pagination-dot`, `.swiper-pagination-bullet`, `.swiper-navigation`, `.swiper-button-prev`, or `.swiper-button-next`. The global partials handle that. Only write **per-block color/theme overrides** when the design demands different colors than the defaults.

```php
<section class="{slug}-section section">
	<div class="container">
		<!-- Slider -->
		<div class="{slug}-slider swiper">
			<div class="swiper-wrapper">
				<div class="slide swiper-slide">
					<!-- slide content -->
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Controls (outside .swiper so they aren't clipped by overflow:hidden) -->
		<?php if ( count( $items ) > 1 ) : ?>
			<div class="swiper-controls">
				<?php get_template_part( 'template-parts/swiper-pagination' ); ?>
				<?php get_template_part( 'template-parts/swiper-navigation' ); ?>
			</div>
		<?php endif; ?>
	</div>
</section>
```

### Key points

- The slider container gets **two classes**: `{slug}-slider` (JS hook) and `swiper` (Swiper core).
- Each slide gets **two classes**: `slide` (styling — scoped by nesting inside `.{slug}-section`) and `swiper-slide` (Swiper core).
- Child class names are **plain** (`.slide`, `.card`) — not BEM (`{slug}__slide`). Uniqueness comes from nesting inside `.{slug}-section` in SCSS.
- The controls wrapper is always `.swiper-controls` — its layout is provided globally by `_swiper-pagination.scss`.
- Pagination + navigation are always rendered via `get_template_part(...)` calls. Never inline the markup, the SVGs, or the wrapper classes.
- Navigation/pagination sit **outside** the `.swiper` wrapper so `overflow: hidden` doesn't clip them.

